cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the problem of adversarial attacks on deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the fields of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the security aspect of deep networks, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the proposed method involves metric learning, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks, and could be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
